<link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/table.css" />
<br><br>
<section id="left">
	<div style="float: left; width: 100%; font-size:2em; font-weight:bold">
Donation # <%=h @donations.id %>
		<div style="float: right; font-size:1em; font-weight:normal">
    		<a href="/donationss/create">+ New donations</a>
    	</div>
	</div>
<div style="clear: both"></div> <br>

<div class="CSSTableGenerator" >
    <form action="/donations/<%= @donations.id %>" method="post">
    <table>
      <thead>
            <td>Initated By:</td><td><%=h @donations.user.name %></td>
      </thead>

      <tr> <td>SKU Offered:</td> <td><%=h @donations.skuout1 %></td> </tr>

      <tr> <td>Offered Amount:</td> <td><%=h @donations.qout1 %></td> </tr>

      <tr> <td>Description:</td> <td><%=h @donations.description %></td> </tr>

      <tr> <td>Deliverer:</td> <td><%=h @donations.deliverer2 %></td> </tr>

      <tr> <td>Recepient:</td> <td>?</td> </tr>

      <tr> <td>Status:</td> 
            <td>
              <% if @donations.user_id == current_user.id %>
                <%= @donations.status1 %>
                <% else %>
                  <% if @donations.status1 == "new" %>
                    <select id="donations_status1" name="donations[status1]">
                      <option value="new">New</option>
                      <option value="accepted">Accept</option>
                      <option value="rejected">Reject!</option>
                    </td>      
                    <tr>
                    <td></td>
                    <td><button type="submit" class="btn btn-success">Update</button></td>
                    </tr>
                  <% else %>
                    <%= @donations.status1 %>
                    </td>
                  <% end %>
              <% end %>      
    </table>


</form>
</div>
</section>

<aside>
  <section id="feed" role="complementary">
  <p>This page shows the details of the donationss as a <i>donations contract which is the main tool for facilitating donations.</i></p>

  <p>The donations is accepted by changing the status to 'Accepted'. Once accepted, this contract will be binding within the NARA system and the other company will be notified to start the delivery or payment process.</p> 
  <p><b>Meaning of donations Methods:</b>
  <ul><li><b>Barter</b> - All SKUs are paid for with SKUs. No cash is involved</li>
    <li><b>Cash</b> - All SKUs are bought with cash. The buyer provides the cash</li>
    <li><b>Semi-barter</b>  - All SKUs are paid partly with SKUs, partly with cash</li>
  </ul>
  <p><b>Meaning of donations Statuses:</b>
  <ul><li><b>New</b> - The donations request has just been created and no action has been taken by the recipient company</li>
    <li><b>Accepted</b> - The recipient company has accepted the terms of the donations contract</li>
    <li><b>Rejected</b>  - The recipient company has rejected the terms of the donations contract</li>
    <li><b>Fulfilled</b> - The donations has been fulfilled</li></ul></p>
  
  </section>
</aside>